Project 1 - Run a simple Web Server Using Docker 

Step 1 - Add the current user to the docker group 

Check the current user:
>> whoami
Check the current user group:
>> groups amith26
Add the current user to the group if he is not present 
>> sudo usermod -aG docker amith26

Step 2 - Check the Docker Installation 
>> docker --version 

Expected output:
amith26@LAPTOP-4DUIV0LS:~$ docker  --version
Docker version 28.2.2, build 28.2.2-0ubuntu1~24.04.1


Step 3 - Pull the Nginx Image from the dockerhub

>> docker pull nginx
This downloads the nginx image from the docker hub to your local repository 

To check the installation of the docker images use 
>> docker images  

Step 4 - Run the containers

Now start the containers
>> docker start -d -p 8080:80 nginx

Expected Output:
bf14cfc8b153fbdf49ddff4766db3590da1369adae3128ce450be086a4deb404

Request flow : 
Browser
   ↓
Your Machine Port 8080
   ↓
Docker Container
   ↓
Nginx running on port 80

Step 4: Check Running Containers 

Use the command
>> docker ps

Expected output:

amith26@LAPTOP-4DUIV0LS:~$  docker ps
lCONTAINER ID   IMAGE     COMMAND                  CREATED              STATUS              PORTS                                     NAMES
bf14cfc8b153   nginx     "/docker-entrypoint.…"   About a minute ago   Up About a minute   0.0.0.0:8080->80/tcp, [::]:8080->80/tcp   nifty_sutherland

Step 5: Connect to the container in the browser
Go to : 
>> http://localhost:8080

YOu should see the nginx sites

Step 6 - Stop the container 

To stop the container you must first know the container ID 
>> docker ps

Then stop it :
>> docker stop <container ID>

Step 7 - Remove Container

>>docker remove <container-ID>


